    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-09-13T08:18:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-09-09T11:45:00-05:00" n="617"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d617">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A 4e/101: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chairman of the American Delegation, China Tariff Revision
                        Commission</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Arnold</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName> [<date
                            ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates"
                            calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1921-09-13T09:18:00-04:00"
                            notBefore="1921-09-09T12:45:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">undated</hi>
                        </date>].<lb/>[Received September 13, 1922—9:18 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Tariff Commission completes labors end September. Chinese propose following
                    prefatory note to completed tariff: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“The publication of the present English version of the tariff is
                            authorized by the Tariff Revision Commission of 1922. This tariff will
                            come into force on the 1st December 1922.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Does Department sanction? American delegation satisfied present revision gives
                    China full 5 percent effective estimated increased revenues on basis last year
                    trade $15,000,000 silver.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Arnold</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
